descriptions: A nice garden with relaxing atmosphere. Aside from traditional Austrian food you might as well order rarely seen dishes like a Langos Burger
An old traditional Austrian restaurant run by a hospitable family for many years. Their masterpieces are Wiener Schnitzel and Gulasch.
They have a large selection of beer and the portion sizes are huge. It is very authentic, everything tastes so yummy.
One of the best places in town to eat ribs! Friendly staff, great prices - you simply feel welcome as soon as you step in.
A wonderful taste experience. Enjoy a nice evening, sitting in a patio with a slightly italian flair and fast waiters.
Tucked into an unassuming side street in the 1st district, Zwölf Apostkeller is a deceptively cavernous old style beer hall, hidden in a centuries old cellar.
A very charming french bistro with living-room atmosphere. Makes you feel cozy and as if you were in a cafe in the middle of Paris.
Carmen, the owner is always making sure, everyone enjoys the atmosphere with the slightly different furnishings. A tasty variety of delicious food!
Along with a glass of french wine you may enjoy traditional french cuisine. You should make a reservation, do that early enough.:-)
An exquisite range of dishes, making you want more. The Rainbow Bowl is highly recommended. Very courteous staff and elegant atmosphere with a bar-flavour.
This fabulous place is packed with lots of different flavoured crepes you simply can't get enough of. Very welcoming and relaxing atmosphere.
With a laid-back though extra-ordinary atmosphere the CouCou attracts its guests. Friendly waiters and even the music makes you wanna stay for another drink after dinner.
Famous for its tasty seafood, this really small and simple place is highly recommended if you are into eating lobster, octopus or local fishes and don't need fancy furnishing.
Italian friends recommended this pearl.Bodulo is one of the best places to go in vienna, if you want to enjoy excellent seafood and a mediterranean atmosphere.
A tiny, simple but addictive location!Tasty scents and a wide variety of seafood wraps, makes your mouth water as soon as you enter. Try one of the delicious salads. It is worth it.
Enjoy a relaxing and wonderful evening at the Nautilus. In the middle of the famous Naschmarkt, this place is a must go if you are into seafood.
Enjoy an impressive variety of fresh fish and family-friendly ambience. Simply delicious! The owners are seemingly happy if their guests enjoy their stay.

Gourmet fish and a relaxing ambience will make you come back to Lubin, one of Vienna's best fish restaurants. It is not only a nice place to have dinner but you can also buy a variety of fish to take home.
Quality paired with very talkative waiters. An addictive combination with a great variety of pizza, noodles and co. Convince yourself that Ruffino is worth a visit.

With a pizza oven shaped like a huge disco ball in the middle of the room, which the restaurant owns its name to, eating pizza becomes an adventure. Rumour has it that even italians admire their pizza-baking-skills!
You want fresh ingredients on a delicious pizza? Then make sure you got to Pizza Randale early enough because in the evenings it is always crowded. The food is just yummy.
Owner Francesco Calò was voted world's best pizza cook in Salerno. Furthermore Via Toledo surprises with innovative Pizza creations. Definitely worth a visit, or two or three....

Vero is said to be Vienna's first organic Pizza restaurant, setting also a new appearance-trend. Oriental lamps mix with industrial ambience. Aside from the full grian pizza you should definitely try the Nutella-pizza if you prefer it sweet.

Surrounded by wooden furniture and maritime decoration, eating Pizza at Mafiosi feels a little bit like being on a pirate ship. Be very hungry when you go there, the portions are large and of course inviting.

A drink and a burger with Rock n'Roll - flair. Sounds tempting? We agree. All the burgers are tasty but the Addicted-Burger not only tastes good but comes with a black bread. Two thumbs up for this small sister of the Hardrock Cafe.
Lots of different burgers with additional ingredients to choose from. Omnom is widespread in Vienna and we are a fan too. Enjoy a fresh-made burger in a relaxing and simple surrounding.
If you are a fan of the Back to the future movies you will love this diner. Have a tasty burger and feel like you woke up in the 50ies. Worth a visit.

One would not expect such delicious burger creations in a restaurant with such misleading name. This is an insider tip from us. The food is marvellous, the furnishing unexpected for a burger location. Check out the extra-ordinary paintings on their wall.
Probably the biggest burgers in town we know. The air smells of barbecue, the street outside a bit noisy but who cares when you are about to bite in a tasty, fresh burger.
A cult place for burger and music lovers. Enjoy tasty burger variations and occasionally you are accompanied by local bands while your eating. Authentic and down to earth.

Trendy indeed. Create your individual bowl, suitable for your taste or choose one of the - as the owner calls it - five palms of Aloha bowls. They are all delicious and rare, so try something new and vegan like the Ponzu Salmon bowl.

The main idea behind Apapika Bowls was the love for travelling and the inspiration of different food cultures. The output - unique and purely fresh bowls with an arabic touch, consumed in a relaxing ambience.
Honu Tiki Bowls are made from the freshest ingredients and designed to make you happy! Signature dish or Build Your Own Bowl? It‘s up to you. Food can be pleasure
The Nana7 promises an explosion of taste in your mouth and this is what you get when you eat a delicious, maybe spicy bowl in a family-like ambience.

The owners of this friendly and passionate restaurant believe that getting together and enjoying food needs to be celebrated. That is why the couple opened up a restaurant in the heart of Vienna with a family-like flair.
If you are looking for healthy wraps, bowls and fresh juices, this is the right place to go to! Very delicious, mostly for takeaway in a lunch break.

If you want a touch of greece and a welcoming atmosphere, go to Odysseus. One of the best Moussakas in town and staff is entertainingly relaxed. Be prepared to get an ouzo on the house when you leave:-).
A very stylish greek restaurant. Aside from the marvellous food the huge photographs of the wall create the feeling of being outside the city on holiday.
A feelgood greek with astonishing starter plates. The fish dishes are also very delicious. Relax and enjoy in a friendly atmosphere!
The friendly enjoys recommending dishes and good wines, always smiling. A nice and cozy atmosphere and focused on traditional greek food.
A traditional greek restaurant in the luxurious 19th district though affordable. The portions could be bigger, but the food is very delicious and worth a taste! Especially the Gyros.
This rather huge greek restaurant is very richly decorated and looks elegant. But the food is affordable and the waiters are very courteous. See for yourself.
Among all kinds of georgian dishes, the turkish specialities at Ansari are highly recommendable. The atmosphere is relaxing and family-friendly.
Mostly for take-away but you can also have a seat and enjoy your food in a small seating area. Stylish food creations and very friendyl staff. Definitely a winner if you enjoy good tastes.
Close to the very vivid Brunnenmarkt is the well-known Kent, with many mouthwatering smells and plenty of dishes to choose from. Getting hungry already.

The smell of barbecue and spices makes you want to order immediately. Diwan is famous for its Döner or Kebab. Though the restaurant itself is not too extravagant. But if you are hungry this will be a very good place to go.
If you are more about getting your mouths on some tasty traditional Turkish food, and less about a fine and fancy dining experience, Sentepe is your go-to for a quick bite.
Traditional turkish cuisine in a comfortable atmosphere. There is also their famous Etli Ekmek ( minced meat on a very thin crispy bread ) and their various Pide variations.
Amidst traditional persian furnishing you can enjoy unspeakably good persian food. The rather extravagant appearance is really worth a visit aside from the dishes of course.
Run by an ambitious family who is still working together in the restaurant after 14 years, the Kolbe is a highly recommended place when it comes to really authentic persian food.
Opinions differ when it comes to Hatam, which already exists in Vienna for over 20 years now. Some say try Kudipeh Kebab. We say try everything there but don't leave without tasting the safran rice.
Arezu chose a more modern persian style of cuisine and is also highly recommandable. You will be surprised of flavours and varieties in this
This mixture of Bar and Restaurant is really appealing. Diving into the world of persian cuisine is tasty there. Also a nice and relaxing ambience.
We discovered this tiny restaurant by coincidence. At noon you can try different persian dishes at a delicious buffet. A secret we share with you ;-).
Although the interior looks a little bit like a traditional viennese so called Gasthaus, they really know their way around when it comes to traditionally spiced chinese food.
This is the place to go if you love dim sum in all varieties. They also have specialties on the menu which change regularly. An elegant way to enjoy chinese dishes.
In the style of a viennese bar the ON is a relaxing place to enjoy your meal. It can definitely compete with traditional chinese restaurants but adding some modern flavours to their menue.
Very modern design and a pleasure spending time there. Aside from the fabulous food you can enjoy the elegant but not too overwhelming atmosphere.
Satisfying price-performance ratio and large portions. Also a good place to go when you are really hungry, aside from the fact, that the appearance of this place is inviting.
Behind No.27 hides a cozy restaurant with focus on szechuan cuisine. Trendy and an enlightening atmosphere will make you want to linger the whole evening.
A mixture of a restaurant and an aesthetic bar, pretty trendy in vienna but yet very hospitable. The spiced chicken is simply marvellous, followed by one of the cocktails they offer.
Traditional mexican cuisine spiced up and suitable for viennese surroundings. Delicious and versatile dishes. Don't forget to eat Churros for dessert.
Santos looks more like a cocktailbar than a restaurant. Very impressive bar interior. It is a pleasure to choose a good drink of choice after a full and wonderful meal.
Trendy and small the Gorilla Kitchen is tempting you to linger and eat more than one burrito or bowl from their exquisite menu. Stylish and simple.
Pancho is a bit similar to Santos according to what they offer but the atmosphere is a little bit more down to earth.
Dona Irma is well-known for its traditional, delicious mexican food. But especially the colorful and innovative interior makes you feel like your are in Mexico for a short time-travel-trip.

titles: Curry Vibes - Spice up your Life!
descriptions: Amidst a rather elegant surrounding enjoy the traditionally spiced dishes that Rani serves, prepared with witt. An explosion of different spices. Simply a pleasure.
Insiders say that at Tulsi they have discovered India's hidden kitchen secrets. Traditional flavours mingle with new interpreted tastes.
A friendly and relaxing ambeince in which you can enjoy a delicious Tandoori Chicken or other indian specialities. High quality food and service.
This higly reccommendable location is a mixture of cozy bar and elegant restaurant, offering a great variety of innovative indian curries.

The owners, an elderly couple with a devotion to food and spices offer a small variety of dishes, a rather extravagant choice. Try Chicken Tikka if you like it spicy or simply go with a delicious curry.
The name indicates a tastful adventure which it is indeed to eat one of the large curry variations or a typically indian dessert. The athmosphere is simple but cozy.
